    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                <pb facs="nei.n1b.5.5"/>
                <note type="curatorial">5</note>
                
                <opener>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>5835 Vine Street</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Lincoln, Nebraska 68505</addrLine> 
                    </address>
                    <dateline>May 30, 1973</dateline>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Miss Linda D. DeLowry</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>111 Carson Drive</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Monroeville, Pennsylvania 15146</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Miss DeLowry:</salute>
                </opener>
                
                <p>Naturally I am interested in yoiur letter of May 21, 1973, regarding the doctoral dissertation you
                are writing on my work.</p> 
                <p>I am swamped with correspondence but I would be willing to answer certain definite questions tha
                tyou might ask me. At present I am working on the second volume of my autobiography (the first being
                ALL IS BUT A BEGINNING) and with the re-cording of my work by United Artists. There will be a series
                of twelve albums, the first of which will appear in August. This has been a difficult and exhausting
                job and is not completed yet.</p> 
                <p>Make your questions as short and definite as you can make them and I will try to dictate concise
                answers.</p> 
                
                <closer>
                    <salute>Wtih every good wish,</salute>
                    <signed>John G. Neihardt </signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="authorial">JGN:nh</note>
                <postscript><p>P.S. Some information sheets are being mailed to you. - J.G.N.</p></postscript>
                
            </div1>
            
        </body>
        
